OL,3,CWhat is a 'recall petition' and why
OL,4,Chas it been triggered?
OL,6,FIf at least 10% of the registered
OL,7,Felectorate sign the petition, then the
OL,8,Fseat becomes vacant which would
OL,9,Ftrigger a by-election.
OL,11,FA recall petition cannot be launched
OL,12,Fif a general election is due to be
OL,13,Fheld within the next six months, and
OL,14,Fit would be halted if an early
OL,15,Felection was called.
OL,17,FIf a sitting MP is convicted of any
OL,18,Foffence and receives a custodial
OL,19,Fsentence of more than a year, they
OL,20,Fautomatically lose their seat.
